The motherboard is the most important part of a computer system, in short it connects each component to eachother. 
The motherboard has BIOS on it, and PCIE slots. It also has slots for RAM modules to be placed in.
When purchasing a motherboard you should consider a few variables, those are listed below:

        - Price for the product
        - Quality of brand
        - BIOS compatibilities
        - Support for DDR4/DDR3
        - Maximum amount of RAM
        - Best RAM to go with the motherboard
